### Apps Script Templating Pattern

Use Google Apps Script's built-in HTML templating for runtime injection:

```javascript
// In your .gs server file:
function showLessonEntryForm() {
  const branding = SITE_CONFIG.branding;
  const template = HtmlService.createTemplateFromFile('LessonEntryForm');
  template.schoolName = branding.schoolName;
  template.tagline = branding.tagline;
  template.logoUrl = branding.logoUrl;
  template.primaryColor = branding.primaryColor;
  template.headerGradientStart = branding.headerGradientStart;
  template.headerGradientEnd = branding.headerGradientEnd;
  const html = template.evaluate().setWidth(800).setHeight(600);
  SpreadsheetApp.getUi().showModalDialog(html, branding.schoolName);
}
```

